IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: See Schedule O. Organization's Mission Statement included in Part III Line 1.
IRS990.MissionDescription: The Babe Ruth Baseball/ Softball Program, using regulation competitive baseball and softball rules, teaches skills, mental and physical development, and respect for the rules of the game, and basic ideals of sportsmanship and fair play. In all aspects, Babe Ruth League Inc is committed to providing our participants the very best educational, sports experience possible. It is our fundamental belief that every child with a desire to play baseball or softball be afforded that opportunity.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The compensation of the CEO is presented to the Finance Committee for review. Once the Finance Committee reviews the compensation it is then presented to the Board of Directors. Each board member votes on whether to approve or decline the compensation.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: At the annual board meeting members are required to review the conflict of interest policy and confirm in writing they do not have a conflict of interest.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Form 990 was reviewed in detail by the CFO prior to filing. An email is sent to all governing body members with a link to a password-protected website in which the entire From 990 can be viewed prior to filing.
